-- India Beats Pakistan by Six Wickets in Cricket’s Asia Cup
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2012-03-18T16:18:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-18/india-beats-pakistan-by-six-wickets-in-cricket-s-asia-cup.html
Virat Kohli scored a century as
 India  beat  Pakistan  by six wickets in today’s Asia Cup one-day
cricket match in Mirpur.  Kohli cracked 183 off 148 balls to lift India to the win
with more than two overs to spare after Pakistan had scored 329-
6. Sachin Tendulkar and Rohit Sharma added half-centuries as
India scored 330-4 in reply.  Pakistan openers Mohammad Hafeez and Nasir Jamshed both
scored more than 100 runs before being dismissed in successive
overs  The Asia Cup also includes Bangladesh and Sri Lanka.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  